Appeal</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Longer version on financial news wire.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOYCE M. ROSENBERG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The fate of <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s hostile $ 12.2 billion bid for <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> rests with the <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> after a judge refused to block Time's $ 14 billion tender offer for <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION> The <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> agreed late Friday to hear the case after <ORGANIZATION> Chancery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> Judge <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> turned down a request by <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> and some of <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION>'s biggest shareholders for an injunction against <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION>'s bid for <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> halted Time's $ 70 a share offer, which had been scheduled to expire at midnight Monday, for 10 days to give Paramount time to appeal his ruling. If Paramount loses, it will pave the way for Time and <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> to merge, forming <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the world's largest communications concern. Paramount, which is offering $ 200 a share for <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION>, has said it would not pursue a buyout of <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION>. Time called <PERSON> Allen </PERSON>'s decision, `` a very big step toward making <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> a reality.'' <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> rejected <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION