<HEAD>Small Plane Crashes, Three Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROMEOVILLE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A single-engine plane smashed into a machine shop shortly after takeoff, killing all three people aboard and injuring two workers at the shop, authorities said. The <ORGANIZATION> Walco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tool </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Engineering </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, which had about 50 employees working at the time of the crash, is about a quarter mile from the runway of <ORGANIZATION> Lewis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airport </ORGANIZATION>. `` There was this gigantic explosion,'' said <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Gladkowski </PERSON>, 40, a machinist at the shop. One of the men, a machinist, was listed in serious condition at a hospital with burns over more than half of his body. Another employee was treated and released. Witnesses said the plane had trouble gaining altitude during takeoff. `` It appeared on takeoff to be unstable and was moving at a low rate toward its climb,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Mort </PERSON> <PERSON> Edelstein </PERSON>. `` Suddenly it took a left turn, went down behind trees, struck a building and exploded into flames.'' The <ORGANIZATION> Walco </ORGANIZATION> building is in a small industrial park located near a pastoral care center run by the <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Archdiocese </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Joliet </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Gladkowski </PERSON> said some employees had just gotten up from eating lunch at a counter where the passenger section of the plane landed on the building. The plane struck a solid beam and did not cause major damage to the building. `` It's a blessing more people were not injured,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Walco </ORGANIZATION> president <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Walsh </PERSON>. `` There could be over a million dollars of machinery damaged, but that does n't matter.''
