hat <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> collected. `` I'm sure he's pretty good at arithmetic and he would recognize that this reflects an awful lot of support, a broad base,'' <PERSON> Dinkins </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Said </PERSON> <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>, who began his political career as a reformer, but twice was reelected with the backing of Democratic powers: `` He's the machine candidate What would you expect?'' There have been other ironies so far in the campaign. <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON>, 45, who built his reputation busting Wall Streeters, mobsters and corrupt officials, found himself last week defending the hiring of three lawyers who admitted having used drugs. <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>, of all people, paraphrased <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> in Thursday's announcement: `` I do n't think God is finished with me yet and I want to do more for this city. Then there is <PERSON> Lauder </PERSON>'s multimillion-dollar television onslaught, in which a voice dripping with disgust calls <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON> a liberal. A complicating factor in the race is the existence in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> of small Conservative and Liberal parties, which enable candidates to run even if they lose one of the two major primaries. <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON> has already been endorsed by the <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, as was Republican <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Lindsay </PERSON> in 1965, and would run on that ticket in addition to the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> ticket if he wins in September. But <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON>'s stance against abortion has reduced his support, the Daily News-WABC-TV poll indicated. Gays have criticized his opposition to <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>'s proposal to extend paid time off to city employees grieving deaths of live-in companions. <PERSON> Lauder </PERSON>, who entered the race at the urging of Republican Sen. <PERSON> Alfonse </PERSON> <PERSON> D'Amato </P