tary vehicles. The Indian spokesman said the Indian soldiers were on foot. However, this seemed unlikely _ especially at in the dark _ because of the danger of guerrilla ambushes and leopard attacks. The Indian peacekeeping force was dispatched to <LOCATION> Sri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lanka </LOCATION> on July 30, 1987, after <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Sri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lanka </LOCATION> signed an accord designed to end the war by Tamil guerrillas fighting for an independent homeland. Tamils comprise 18 percent of <LOCATION> Sri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lanka </LOCATION>'s 16 million people and say they are discriminated against by the Sinhalese-dominated government. Sinhalese make up 75 percent of the population. <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> became involved in the internal affairs of its small neighbor because of its role as the region's chief power and the political clout of its own Tamil minority of 60 million.
