said authorities found 35 guns, many of them loaded, in a search of Root's plane last April at the <LOCATION> Manassas </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>. All of the guns were legal under federal law, and all but one under state law, which led to a state misdemeanor charge. The arsenal included assault-style rifles and three .357 - caliber Magnum In <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION>, Secretary of State <PERSON> Rufus </PERSON> <PERSON> Edmisten </PERSON> said his office has been investigating security fraud allegations against a company with which Root acted as an attorney. <PERSON> Edmisten </PERSON> said the lawyer knew he was under investigation.
